==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From [[Cantonese]] [[鬼佬]] ("foreign devil", literally "[[ghost]] man").  
===Noun===
[[Category:English nouns]]
'''gweilo'''
#(''derogatory'') [[w:Caucasian race|Caucasian]] people (generally men)

====Usage====
For the usage in Cantonese, see the usage notes at [[鬼佬]].

Some Caucasians living in [[w:Hong Kong|Hong Kong]] now occasionally use the English '''gweilo''' to jokingly refer to themselves.  This reflects a transformation in which an ethnic group begins referring to itself with a term which was originally considered an [[w:ethnic slur|ethnic slur]].

In the Hong Kong cinema industry, '''gweilo''' is often used to describe Caucasian actors playing in Asian movies.
